cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper addresses the problem of privacy policy and privacy architecture design, which is a fundamental aspect of security and cryptography.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper focuses on two relevant aspects of privacy, namely, accountability and personal data control, which are important issues in the intersection of computers and society.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a systematic design approach of privacy policies and an automated privacy architectures generation method, which are relevant to software engineering.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a high-level policy language and an architecture language, which are relevant to programming languages.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper demonstrates the usability of the proposed approach on real-world systems such as Facebook, which is relevant to social and information networks.
